<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g0690f878-b8a6-4156-8bf8-3b5018d65694"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g0690f878-b8a6-4156-8bf8-3b5018d65694">ha-</a></span><span lang="sea" style="font-weight:bold;font-size:58%;position:relative;top:0.3em;"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g0690f878-b8a6-4156-8bf8-3b5018d65694">1</a></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="morphtypes"><span class="morphtype"><span class="abbreviation"><span lang="ms">awl</span></span></span></span><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="en"><span lang="ms">kk</span><span lang="en">:Any</span></span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g0690f878-b8a6-4156-8bf8-3b5018d65694"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">awak; anda; kamu; imbuhan ganti nama diri kedua tunggal untuk kata kerja</span><span lang="en">you; 2nd person singular agreement marker for verb</span></span><span class="lexsensereferences"><span class="lexsensereference"><span class="ownertype_name"><span lang="ms">sinonim</span></span><span class="configtargets"><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g34cd3988-796e-40fd-9659-a0c87cd06bdd">hek</a></span><span lang="sea" style="font-weight:bold;font-size:58%;position:relative;top:0.3em;"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g34cd3988-796e-40fd-9659-a0c87cd06bdd">2</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Hek ya hapanei muh eng.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Kamu sudah tahu nama saya.</span><span lang="en">You already know my name.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gf3f3d691-7b00-446d-991d-cd599da978b3"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gf3f3d691-7b00-446d-991d-cd599da978b3">ha-</a></span><span lang="sea" style="font-weight:bold;font-size:58%;position:relative;top:0.3em;"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gf3f3d691-7b00-446d-991d-cd599da978b3">2</a></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="morphtypes"><span class="morphtype"><span class="abbreviation"><span lang="ms">awl</span></span></span></span><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="en"><span lang="ms">kk</span><span lang="en">:Any</span></span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="gf3f3d691-7b00-446d-991d-cd599da978b3"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">mahu</span><span lang="en">to want</span></span><span class="lexsensereferences"><span class="lexsensereference"><span class="ownertype_name"><span lang="ms">sinonim</span></span><span class="configtargets"><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g8d53281a-bdf0-4bc6-aa0f-024981154927">hu-</a></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Amek kiurok nu wak eng, "Entah hahod tarog adeh, kotle."</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Ibu berkata kepada makcik saya, "Jika kamu mahu pucuk ubi ini, ambillah."</span><span lang="en">My mother said to my auntie, "If you want this tapioca shoot, (just) take it."</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="ga0c3d027-ef8b-4b7a-a2b9-108f2b0b185f"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/ga0c3d027-ef8b-4b7a-a2b9-108f2b0b185f">haah</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata sifat</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="ga0c3d027-ef8b-4b7a-a2b9-108f2b0b185f"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">ya</span><span lang="en">yes</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">"Mongka hek neh hakep kak?" bitanya ya Wak Risan. "Haah, mong nek memerip ikor taleh," engrok Wah Ika.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">"Kamu ada dapat ikan?" Wak Risan bertanya. "Ya, hanya ada beberapa ekor saja," Wak Ika menjawab.</span><span lang="en">"Did you catch any fish?"  Wak Risan asked. "Yes, only a few," Wak Ika replied.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="ge302a8e2-a2d4-4bbb-853c-484cd3a05671"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/ge302a8e2-a2d4-4bbb-853c-484cd3a05671">habar</a></span></span><span class="etymologies"><span class="etymology"><span class="languages"><span class="language"><span class="abbreviation-2"><span lang="ms">BM</span></span></span></span><span class="form"><span lang="ms">khabar</span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata nama</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="ge302a8e2-a2d4-4bbb-853c-484cd3a05671"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">khabar</span><span lang="en">news</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Ma ihabar engkek nek?</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Kamu semua apa khabar?</span><span lang="en">How are you all doing?</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g103fb8e8-4366-4fa5-ad60-b9718ad50497"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g103fb8e8-4366-4fa5-ad60-b9718ad50497">habu</a></span></span><span class="etymologies"><span class="etymology"><span class="languages"><span class="language"><span class="abbreviation-2"><span lang="ms">BM</span></span></span></span><span class="form"><span lang="ms">habuk</span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata nama</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g103fb8e8-4366-4fa5-ad60-b9718ad50497"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">abu; debu; debu; sisa sesuatu objek atau lain-lain benda yang habis terbakar</span><span lang="en">ashes</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Cok ajeh kigemar dak ku kemil habuk.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Anjing itu suka tidur atas abu.</span><span lang="en">That dog likes to sleep on the ashes.</span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">"Agok man habuk ajeh, kutor!" amek kiles ha menang eng.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">"Jangan main abu itu, kotor!" ibu memarahi adik saya.</span><span lang="en">"Don't play with those ashes, They are dirty!" mother scolded my young brother.</span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Kucig ajeh kicooh ku habuk wal. </span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Kucing itu berak di abu dapur.</span><span lang="en">The cat pooped on the stove ash.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g2c35428c-10b8-4bb7-bdea-e6835a2eeba8"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g2c35428c-10b8-4bb7-bdea-e6835a2eeba8">had</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata keterangan</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sensenumber" lang="en">1</span><span class="sense" entryguid="g2c35428c-10b8-4bb7-bdea-e6835a2eeba8"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">hanya; cuma; sekadar; setakat</span><span lang="en">just; only; in a limit</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Apak eng pek dij isekulah, kisekulah had lei derjah 5 taleh. Tapi ha kerana rajet kikerakjak, ilei bihok ya itukeh. Jap tahut igaji biperhuj ru selalo biog bonus.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Bapa saya tidak tamat persekolahan, dia bersekolah cuma sehingga darjah 5. Tetapi oleh kerana dia rajin bekerja, dia disayangi oleh bosnya. Setiap tahun gajinya dinaikan dan selalu memerolehi bonus.</span><span lang="en">My father did not finish school, he only went to school until grade 5. But because he was hard-working, he was loved by his boss. His salary is increased every year and he always earns bonuses.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sensenumber" lang="en">2</span><span class="sense" entryguid="g2c35428c-10b8-4bb7-bdea-e6835a2eeba8"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">sangat; amat</span><span lang="en">very</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Kenon eng ihad kisengoh ha chok medei ilei pernah bikap mase lekat kisanget.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Anak saya sangat takut terhadap anjing kerana dia pernah digigit semasa beliau masih kecil.</span><span lang="en">My son is very scared of dogs because he was bitten when he was young.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gaed2ea80-318e-45d7-94aa-8f8a864f24a6"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gaed2ea80-318e-45d7-94aa-8f8a864f24a6">hadang</a></span></span><span class="etymologies"><span class="etymology"><span class="languages"><span class="language"><span class="abbreviation-2"><span lang="ms">BM</span></span></span></span><span class="form"><span lang="ms">halang</span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata kerja</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="gaed2ea80-318e-45d7-94aa-8f8a864f24a6"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">menghalang; menahan supaya tidak dapat bergerak</span><span lang="en">to block</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Bah Peran kibesat nu eng, "Nong nu Cameron Highland ya bihadang, biget joi ku arik adeh medei mong garaj. Kelemnek manik lebat lei mong jeoi garaj ku nong ajeh."</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Bah Peran berpesan kepada saya, "Jalan itu ke Cameron Highland dihalang, tidak dibenarkan mengikuti jalan tersebut kerana terdapat tanah runtuh. Malan tadi hujan lebat sehingga ada banyak (kejadian) tanah runtuh di (sepanjang) jalan tersebut."</span><span lang="en">Bah Peran gave advice to me, "the road to Cameron Highlands has been blocked, that road cannot be used because there has been a landslide. Last night it rained heavily and lots of earth slid onto that road."</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g6f26b006-7e6f-465e-b8e8-1cd332a91a88"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g6f26b006-7e6f-465e-b8e8-1cd332a91a88">hadap</a></span></span><span class="etymologies"><span class="etymology"><span class="languages"><span class="language"><span class="abbreviation-2"><span lang="ms">BM</span></span></span></span><span class="form"><span lang="ms">hadap</span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata kerja</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g6f26b006-7e6f-465e-b8e8-1cd332a91a88"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">hadap; berdepan</span><span lang="en">to be facing; to be face-to-face</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Mase ubai bitermuk, Wak Ani ru Bah Meran ubai gei behadap sebegei tanda ubai ajeh kenah-gensir.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Semasa mereka dijodohkan, Wak Ani dan Bah Meran mereka berdua duduk menghadap (satu dengan yang lain) sebagai tanda mereka berdua itu suami-isteri.</span><span lang="en">When they got married, Wak Ani and Bah Meran sat face-to-face as a sign that they were husband and wife.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g26178818-177c-499a-98e3-bae6baa6fead"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g26178818-177c-499a-98e3-bae6baa6fead">hag</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata sifat</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g26178818-177c-499a-98e3-bae6baa6fead"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">sembuh</span><span lang="en">healed; to heal up</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Amek kitanya nu tenek eng, "Ya hagka temak kenon hek?"</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Ibu bertanya pada kakak saya, "Sudah sembuhkah kudis (pada) anak kamu?"</span><span lang="en">Mother asked my sister, "has your son's scabies healed?"</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g9ba1d02a-b5d5-46db-a6df-59eb33d82b15"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g9ba1d02a-b5d5-46db-a6df-59eb33d82b15">hai</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata kerja</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g9ba1d02a-b5d5-46db-a6df-59eb33d82b15"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">menjerit; menengking</span><span lang="en">to scream; to shout; to snarl; to scold</span></span><span class="lexsensereferences"><span class="lexsensereference"><span class="ownertype_name"><span lang="ms">sinonim</span></span><span class="configtargets"><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g89afb48e-47c4-4a3b-8206-a851b7c81180">karau</a></span></span></span><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g923b203e-9048-45b0-b20c-3c88df528474">kerker</a></span></span></span><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/ge33afaf2-87c6-421e-89bb-52672a5e93a3">wig</a></span><span lang="sea" style="font-weight:bold;font-size:58%;position:relative;top:0.3em;"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/ge33afaf2-87c6-421e-89bb-52672a5e93a3">2</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Apak eng kiurok nu bah eng, "Agok panhai, mabek sanget doh naisengoh."</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Bapa saya berkata kepada pakcik saya, "Jangan terlampau menengking, nanti kanak-kanak menjadi takut."</span><span lang="en">My father said to my uncle, "Don't shout too loud! The kids will be scared."</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g4248fe32-ab08-4212-a0be-7da4dff5f9a9"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g4248fe32-ab08-4212-a0be-7da4dff5f9a9">hajap</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata kerja</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g4248fe32-ab08-4212-a0be-7da4dff5f9a9"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">miskin; daif; papa kedana</span><span lang="en">to be extremely poor; to be destitute</span></span><span class="lexsensereferences"><span class="lexsensereference"><span class="ownertype_name"><span lang="ms">sinonim</span></span><span class="configtargets"><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gd2a379d0-bffe-492d-b0f9-509c8e39d3d9">dadat</a></span></span></span><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gfa5c6cd0-1a18-4477-af2f-0d8ee3273eb3">susah</a></span></span></span><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g831d7222-9186-4744-859e-4c8c2ffe7743">terek</a></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Bah Mat ajeh, hamapen kihajap tapi pek pernah kisengmanj nu mai.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Walaupun Bah Mat miskin, tetapi dia tidak pernah meminta-minta kepada orang lain.</span><span lang="en">Even though Bah Mat is poor, he has never begged from other people.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gc0bda505-7d96-4712-a90f-0b8d3a211034"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gc0bda505-7d96-4712-a90f-0b8d3a211034">hakem</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata nama</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="gc0bda505-7d96-4712-a90f-0b8d3a211034"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">hakim</span><span lang="en">judge</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="minorentrycomplex left" id="g09b6e983-41e5-4ac7-976d-fd29fac3ab7a"><span class="headword-5"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g09b6e983-41e5-4ac7-976d-fd29fac3ab7a">hakhok</a></span></span><span class="complexformentryrefs"><span class="complexformentryref"><span class="referencedentries"><span class="referencedentry"><span class="headword-6"><span lang="sea"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gc5f02c4b-438b-48c0-8422-896ecdf9608d">hok</a></span><span lang="sea" style="font-weight:bold;font-size:58%;position:relative;top:0.3em;"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gc5f02c4b-438b-48c0-8422-896ecdf9608d">1</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="minorentrycomplex left" id="g9459ebba-3541-497c-ba18-ba9748fded91"><span class="headword-5"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g9459ebba-3541-497c-ba18-ba9748fded91">haknok</a></span><span><audio id="ghaknok-63729602186872"><source src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/cloud-storage.webonary.org/semai/AudioVisual/haknok-63729602186872.mp3"></source></audio><a class="sea-Zxxx-x-audio" href="#ghaknok-63729602186872" onclick="if (!window.__cfRLUnblockHandlers) return false; document.getElementById('ghaknok-63729602186872').play()" data-cf-modified-8b25f7b663783d959b313118-=""> </a></span></span><span class="complexformentryrefs"><span class="complexformentryref"><span class="referencedentries"><span class="referencedentry"><span class="headword-6"><span lang="sea"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gc5f02c4b-438b-48c0-8422-896ecdf9608d">hok</a></span><span lang="sea" style="font-weight:bold;font-size:58%;position:relative;top:0.3em;"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gc5f02c4b-438b-48c0-8422-896ecdf9608d">1</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g3fe706e7-6449-41fb-a638-b8a271b9e561"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g3fe706e7-6449-41fb-a638-b8a271b9e561">hal</a></span></span><span class="etymologies"><span class="etymology"><span class="languages"><span class="language"><span class="abbreviation-2"><span lang="ms">BM</span></span></span></span><span class="form"><span lang="ms">hal</span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata nama</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g3fe706e7-6449-41fb-a638-b8a271b9e561"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">hal; sesuatu yang terjadi; peristiwa atau kejadian</span><span lang="en">affair, matter</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">"Ma-ma hal doh pasalle nu eng," tuan deg ajeh kiurok nu eng.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">"Apa-apa hal nanti bagitahu saya," tuan rumah itu berkata kepada saya.</span><span lang="en">"If there is any issue, just let me know," the landlord said to me.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gac3b4dc3-d9a1-4bb0-90fe-7d4730de5544"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gac3b4dc3-d9a1-4bb0-90fe-7d4730de5544">halak</a></span><span lang="sea" style="font-weight:bold;font-size:58%;position:relative;top:0.3em;"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gac3b4dc3-d9a1-4bb0-90fe-7d4730de5544">1</a></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata nama</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="gac3b4dc3-d9a1-4bb0-90fe-7d4730de5544"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">bomoh; dukun; pawang</span><span lang="en">witch doctor; shaman</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Ku jaman entem, amen mai nainyaknyik, enai naiet nu halak dea biterbor. Tapi hunen, ya kurang mai naituju nu halak medei ya mong hospitel.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Pada zaman dahulu, jika orang merasa sakit, mereka akan pergi (berjumpa) bomoh supaya disembuhkan. Tetapi sekarang, sudah kurang orang berjumpa bomoh kerana sudah ada hospital.</span><span lang="en">In old days, when people got sick, they went to a shaman to be healed. But now, there are few who go to see a shaman, because there is a hospital already.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gdd28641e-dc78-4194-ac76-6a9d62dd032c"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gdd28641e-dc78-4194-ac76-6a9d62dd032c">halak</a></span><span lang="sea" style="font-weight:bold;font-size:58%;position:relative;top:0.3em;"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gdd28641e-dc78-4194-ac76-6a9d62dd032c">2</a></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata seru</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="gdd28641e-dc78-4194-ac76-6a9d62dd032c"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">panggilan hormat oleh seorang lelaki kepada adik ipar lelaki dan abang iparnya</span><span lang="en">terms for a man to address his brother-in-law</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="geb35aa72-fb1a-4f2a-acee-08abfe5db228"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/geb35aa72-fb1a-4f2a-acee-08abfe5db228">halau</a></span></span><span class="etymologies"><span class="etymology"><span class="languages"><span class="language"><span class="abbreviation-2"><span lang="ms">BM</span></span></span></span><span class="form"><span lang="ms">halau</span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata kerja</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="geb35aa72-fb1a-4f2a-acee-08abfe5db228"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">halau; usir</span><span lang="en">to shoo; to chase or drive away</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Amek eng kihalau cok, kinyek doh kidak ku simen.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Ibu saya menghalau anjing, (kerana) dia tidak mahu (anjing tersebut) tidur di (lantai) simen (rumah).</span><span lang="en">My mother shooed the dog away, because she didn't want it to sleep on the cement floor of the house.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gddb92e71-df7b-4b23-92d0-947fab4e1d6b"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gddb92e71-df7b-4b23-92d0-947fab4e1d6b">halei</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata keterangan</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="gddb92e71-df7b-4b23-92d0-947fab4e1d6b"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">seorang diri; berseorangan; keseorangan</span><span lang="en">alone; oneself; by oneself</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Eng nggei nghalei ku padeg.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Saya tinggal seorang diri di rumah.</span><span lang="en">I live by myself at home.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gd5ff6545-d682-45c0-bf26-d9f272ec31a8"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gd5ff6545-d682-45c0-bf26-d9f272ec31a8">halek</a></span></span><span class="dialectlabelsrs"><span class="dialectlabelsr"><span class="name"><span lang="sea">Gopeng</span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata sifat</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="gd5ff6545-d682-45c0-bf26-d9f272ec31a8"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">tidak mengapa</span><span lang="en">why not; no matter</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">"Halek, pek ma. Buleh ngbeh ya lieng."</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">"Tidak mengapa, saya boleh buat sendiri."</span><span lang="en">"Never mind, I can do it myself."</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gaa4401d8-8e3d-4f0d-ba12-a0cb0f860c67"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gaa4401d8-8e3d-4f0d-ba12-a0cb0f860c67">ham</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata kerja</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sensenumber" lang="en">1</span><span class="sense" entryguid="gaa4401d8-8e3d-4f0d-ba12-a0cb0f860c67"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">memetik (sayur-sayuran, pucuk-pucuk daun dsb.)</span><span lang="en">to pick or pluck; to harvest (vegetables, leaf shoots, etc.)</span></span><span class="lexsensereferences"><span class="lexsensereference"><span class="ownertype_name"><span lang="ms">sinonim</span></span><span class="configtargets"><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gab827a29-1abe-4476-9119-ebccf0873389">leh</a></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">"Bulehka eng ngham lada ku selai hek? Lada ku selai eng ya dij," Wak Ros kisemanj ku amek eng.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">"Bolehkah saya memetik cili yang ada di kebun kamu? Cili di kebun saya sudah habis," Wak Ros meminta kepada ibu saya.</span><span lang="en">"Can I pick the peppers that are in your garden? The peppers in my garden are already gone," Wak Ros asked my mother.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sensenumber" lang="en">2</span><span class="sense" entryguid="gaa4401d8-8e3d-4f0d-ba12-a0cb0f860c67"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">ambil</span><span lang="en">to take; to get; to fetch</span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">"Bei tulog amek ham teu," amek kiurok nu jik.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">"Mari tolong ibu mengambil air," ibu berkata kepada kami.</span><span lang="en">"Come and help me fetch water," mother said to us.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g62696df2-69a3-4273-ab07-b05ee05bd93a"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g62696df2-69a3-4273-ab07-b05ee05bd93a">hama</a></span></span><span class="variantformentrybackrefs"><span class="variantformentrybackref"><span class="headword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gf112ec9d-5903-4e82-940c-e6ddccd77466">hamo</a></span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata tanya</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g62696df2-69a3-4273-ab07-b05ee05bd93a"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">kenapa; mengapa; untuk menanyakan sebab untuk seseuatu perkara atau hal</span><span lang="en">why</span></span><span class="lexsensereferences"><span class="lexsensereference"><span class="ownertype_name"><span lang="ms">sinonim</span></span><span class="configtargets"><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g358a3226-a1d7-43bc-9261-b0f0c3309ab8">lama</a></span></span></span><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/ge29da90d-f788-4b7f-9a78-f6a8eec1e2ff">yama</a></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">"Hama hek jap?" tenek eng kitanya.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">"Kenapa kamu menangis?" abang saya bertanya.</span><span lang="en">"Why are you crying?" my older brother asked.</span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Hama ilei kijar nu kerop deg ajeh? </span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Kenapa dia lari ke bawah rumah itu?</span><span lang="en">Why did he run under the house?</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="gd4c04bf8-e021-4cf9-b9ed-441a28bdc4f6"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/gd4c04bf8-e021-4cf9-b9ed-441a28bdc4f6">hamapen</a></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata hubung</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="gd4c04bf8-e021-4cf9-b9ed-441a28bdc4f6"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">walaupun; meskipun</span><span lang="en">even though; although</span></span><span class="lexsensereferences"><span class="lexsensereference"><span class="ownertype_name"><span lang="ms">sinonim</span></span><span class="configtargets"><span class="configtarget"><span class="headword-2"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g6518c04e-c61e-4395-becc-ee1bca7ce2b9">alaupen</a></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="examplescontents"><span class="examplescontent"><span class="example"><span lang="sea">Hamapen ilei kinyik, tapi Wak Selai lekat kaha-kerakjak juga.</span></span><span class="translationcontents"><span class="translationcontent"><span class="translation"><span lang="ms">Walaupun dia demam, tetapi Wak Selai masih mahu bekerja.</span><span lang="en">Even though she is feeling feverish, Wak Selai still wants to work.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>
<div class="post"><div class="entry left" id="g20915926-6528-4f13-9c2f-abdcbe1d9eac"><span class="mainheadword"><span lang="sea"><a href="https://www.webonary.org/semai/g20915926-6528-4f13-9c2f-abdcbe1d9eac">hambe</a></span></span><span class="etymologies"><span class="etymology"><span class="languages"><span class="language"><span class="abbreviation-2"><span lang="ms">BM</span></span></span></span><span class="form"><span lang="ms">hamba</span></span></span></span><span class="senses"><span class="sharedgrammaticalinfo"><span class="morphosyntaxanalysis"><span class="graminfoname"><span lang="ms">kata nama</span></span></span></span><span class="sensecontent"><span class="sense" entryguid="g20915926-6528-4f13-9c2f-abdcbe1d9eac"><span class="definitionorgloss"><span lang="ms">hamba</span><span lang="en">slave</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>

</div>
